---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContactCTA from '../../components/ContactCTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="HBO — Jason Ferrara">
  <article class="case-study">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="container hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-copy">
          <img src="/images/hbo/HBO_logo.svg" alt="HBO" class="hero-logo" />
          <h1>Scaling HBO's Transition to Streaming</h1>
          <div class="hero-meta">
            <span class="meta-detail">UX Design Manager</span>
            <span class="meta-sep">/</span>
            <span class="meta-detail">2013&ndash;2019</span>
          </div>
          <p>HBO was undergoing a fundamental shift &mdash; from premium cable network to direct-to-consumer streaming platform. The organization was evolving from linear programming to on-demand digital experiences across web, mobile, and connected TV ecosystems.</p>
          <p>I led a team of designers responsible for content discovery and playback experiences during the launch and expansion of HBO NOW, helping establish the cross-device foundations that later evolved into HBO Max.</p>
          <p>HBO NOW launched across <strong>20+ device ecosystems</strong>, requiring cohesive experience standards across web, native mobile, and connected television platforms.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-visual">
          <img src="/images/projects/hbo-ia-hero.png" alt="HBO NOW — redesigned connected TV top shelf" class="hero-device-img" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Cross-Device Platform Scale -->
    <section class="cs-section cs-section-alt container">
      <span class="cs-label">Cross-Device Platform Scale</span>
      <h2 class="cs-heading">Cross-Device Platform Scale</h2>
      <p class="cs-intro">The transition to streaming required more than feature delivery &mdash; it required architectural clarity across devices with fundamentally different interaction models.</p>
      <p class="cs-intro cs-intro-secondary">I led the development of scalable information architecture and cross-device UX standards to ensure consistency while respecting the nuances of each platform.</p>

      <div class="impact-grid impact-grid-3col">
        <div class="impact-metric">
          <span class="impact-delta">20+</span>
          <span class="impact-label">Device Ecosystems Supported</span>
        </div>
        <div class="impact-metric">
          <span class="impact-delta">5</span>
          <span class="impact-label">Designers Led at Peak</span>
        </div>
        <div class="impact-metric">
          <span class="impact-delta">Multi-Surface</span>
          <span class="impact-label">Web, Mobile, Connected TV</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <span class="cs-sublabel">Focus Areas</span>

      <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Cross-Device Experience Architecture</h3>
          <p>Defined scalable navigation and content discovery frameworks that adapted across desktop, native mobile, and connected TV environments. Established shared patterns that reduced fragmentation and created a cohesive HBO experience regardless of device.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Streaming Discovery & Playback Optimization</h3>
          <p>Led design of core discovery and playback features that supported the transition from linear browsing to on-demand streaming. Balanced editorial storytelling with usability and performance requirements across platforms.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>HBO NOW Launch & Expansion</h3>
          <p>Directed cross-platform design delivery for HBO NOW, ensuring cohesive execution across 20+ device ecosystems. Navigated platform constraints, certification requirements, and evolving streaming standards during a high-visibility product launch.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <h3>Organizational Maturation</h3>
          <p>Managed and mentored a team of five designers during rapid platform expansion. Established quality standards, strengthened cross-functional collaboration with Product and Engineering, and increased design credibility during HBO's digital transformation.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <ContactCTA />

  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Page Gradient */
  .case-study {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #d9dce6 0%, #edeef3 35%, #f0eee9 65%, #f7f5f2 100%);
  }

  /* Hero */
  .hero {
    padding: 8rem 0 5rem;
  }

  .hero-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.2fr;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .hero-logo {
    height: 35px;
    width: auto;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .hero-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
  }

  .meta-detail {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .meta-sep {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--color-border);
  }

  .hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 1.05;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .hero-copy > p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  /* Hero Visual */
  .hero-visual {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .hero-device-img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  /* Section */
  .cs-section {
    padding-top: 5rem;
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
  }

  .cs-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .cs-heading {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .cs-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 42rem;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .cs-intro-secondary {
    margin-top: -2.5rem;
  }

  .cs-section-alt {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .cs-sublabel {
    display: block;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    padding-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  /* Features Grid */
  .features-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .feature h3 {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .feature p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  /* Impact */
  .impact-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 3.5rem 4rem;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .impact-grid-3col {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  }

  .impact-metric {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .impact-delta {
    font-size: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .impact-label {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .hero-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 3rem;
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 5rem 0 3rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .features-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 2rem;
    }

    .impact-grid {
      gap: 2.5rem 2rem;
    }

    .impact-grid-3col {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
